# E2E Test Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values

# WordPress site URL (no trailing slash)
E2E_BASE_URL=https://pet4.cope.zone

# WordPress admin credentials (must have manage_options capability)
E2E_WP_USERNAME=
E2E_WP_PASSWORD=

# URL of a WordPress page containing all PET shortcodes (for shortcode tests)
# E2E_SHORTCODE_PAGE_URL=https://pet4.cope.zone/e2e-test-shortcodes/

# ── Portal tests ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Portal tests require a WordPress page at /portal containing the [pet_portal]
# shortcode. global-setup navigates to /portal to extract petSettings (nonce +
# apiUrl), then provisions 3 test staff users (sales/hr/manager) with the role
# capabilities pet_sales, pet_hr, pet_manager.
#
# Test users are created with email addresses ending in @pet.internal and are
# hard-deleted by global-teardown after the test run.
#
# No additional env vars are needed — the admin credentials above are used for
# provisioning. The portal test password is hardcoded in global-setup.ts.
